Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.42,0:02:00.42,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:120420,120420}"The Miracle Worker" opened its curtain with a double cast of Maya and Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:06.82,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:126826,126826}The first day was successful with Ayumi's perfect acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.16,0:02:12.16,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:132165,132165}And now the second night, after Ayumi's overwhelming act, Maya appears on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.09,0:02:27.06,Episode title,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:140097,147064}{\an5\pos(766,720)\fscy95\blur1\fad(700,500)}—Episode 21—\NNominated for\NBest Supporting Actress
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.58,0:02:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:150583,150583}Today is finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.58,0:02:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:152585,152585}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.02,0:02:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:155021,155021}Look at how much less of an audience is here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:157590,157590}It's because this actress playing Helen is less known.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.46,0:02:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:160460,160460}Look at this. Even most of the flowers are addressed to Himekawa Utako and Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.80,0:02:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:169803,169803}Quality rather than quantity, it's how much of our heart we put in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.83,0:02:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:172839,172839}Excuse me, here's a delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.27,0:02:57.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:177277,177277}What's wrong, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.54,0:03:00.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:180547,180547}I'm nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.68,0:03:02.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:182682,182682}I'm afraid to be compared with Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.35,0:03:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:186353,186353}Maya!\NCome look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.68,0:03:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:188688,188688}Hurry, Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.08,0:03:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:189089,189089}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.22,0:03:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:196229,196229}Wow, look at the size of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.89,0:03:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:199899,199899}Maya, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.70,0:03:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:202702,202702}"I'm looking forward\Nto seeing your Helen."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.27,0:03:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:207273,207273}He's here!\NMr. Purple Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.64,0:03:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:209642,209642}He's looking, somewhere in this big hall…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.91,0:03:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:212912,212912}…for my… my Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.94,0:03:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:215949,215949}Yes.\NYour Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:219786,219786}Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.45,0:03:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:221454,221454}Maya, it seems like you're calmer now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.72,0:03:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:221721,221721}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.92,0:03:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:223923,223923}I'm looking forward to your Helen as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.69,0:03:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:226693,226693}Teacher…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:228628,228628}A miracle is not something that just happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:230797,230797}You make it happen,\Nwith your own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.13,0:03:53.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:233133,233133}A miracle is something I make\Nhappen with my own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.91,0:04:04.91,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:244911,244911}"The Miracle Worker," played by\NMaya and Utako, has started.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.99,0:04:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:256990,256990}Young lady,\Nit's your day off today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.76,0:04:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:260760,260760}Please, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.56,0:04:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:263563,263563}Thank you for coming,\NMs. Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:266232,266232}This is my husband.\NThis is Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:268201,268201}Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:29.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:269035,269035}Mr. Purple Rose.\NI'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.00,0:04:32.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:272005,272005}I'm not scared anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.70,0:04:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:275709,275709}Since when did this country became so big?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.36,0:04:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:296363,296363}Where should I put the suitcase, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.33,0:04:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298331,298331}Let's put it somewhere convenient for Ms. Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.30,0:05:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:301301,301301}Yes, that will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.73,0:05:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:302736,302736}Where's Helen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.67,0:05:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:303670,303670}I'll take the suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.80,0:05:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:305805,305805}No, I can carry it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.60,0:05:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:307607,307607}Oh no, I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.61,0:05:16.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316616,316616}This girl seems so different from practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.01,0:05:19.01,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:319019,319019}She seems like a totally different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.28,0:05:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:322288,322288}That's Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.52,0:05:23.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:323523,323523}Oh no, it was my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.30,0:05:41.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:341307,341307}This is it: this breath, this rhythm,\Nthe tension and the calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:47.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:347947,347947}The actor who can capture that,\Ncan grab the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.98,0:05:50.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:350984,350984}This girl doesn't know that yet,\Nbut her instinct does.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.69,0:05:58.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:358692,358692}She's leading.\NThis is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.12,0:06:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:362128,362128}Here, Helen.\NLet's start with the doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.46,0:06:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:366466,366466}D·O·L·L.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.50,0:06:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:369502,369502}A doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.54,0:06:19.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379546,379546}What happened?\NI moved from her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.18,0:06:22.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382182,382182}She's supposed to slap me\Nin this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.48,0:06:25.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:385485,385485}What happened to Utako?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.35,0:06:28.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:388355,388355}She's taken by Maya's pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395662,395662}Strange. I can see the darkness around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.33,0:06:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:398331,398331}The darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.73,0:06:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:399733,399733}The darkness… the kind of darkness that Helen, who was blind and deaf, was feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.57,0:06:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:405572,405572}The darkness that Helen was feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.44,0:06:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:408441,408441}There's plenty of light,\Nbut by looking at her movement…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.31,0:06:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:412312,412312}…it makes me feel blinded\Nto the things around her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.95,0:06:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:416950,416950}But, her movement is not like Helen, or at least not what's known to be Helen's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.46,0:07:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:430463,430463}Just because Helen is being played by a different actress makes it a whole new play.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:14.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:434634,434634}Maya, you're great.\NWonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:18.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:438471,438471}They say a play is alive,\Nbut you truly are alive now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.11,0:07:24.11,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:444110,444110}Helen and the lady teacher, Sullivan,\Nnothing was changed from the script…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.81,0:07:30.81,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:450817,450817}…but Utako was feeling that the play was going in an entirely different direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.55,0:07:38.55,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:458558,458558}The first act was finally over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.66,0:07:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462662,462662}Are you okay, Utako?\NYou're sweating.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.56,0:07:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:466566,466566}Mr. Onodera, I have a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.80,0:07:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467801,467801}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.17,0:07:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:470170,470170}I want you to let me take control of this play.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.33,0:07:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:472339,472339}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.94,0:07:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473940,473940}I want to fight her Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.01,0:07:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:477010,477010}No ordinary Sullivan\Ncan fight against her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.28,0:08:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:480280,480280}With her, I can not just act.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.61,0:08:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:483616,483616}I've noticed that I'm not acting, but being real.\NThis is the first time this has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.82,0:08:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:487821,487821}I'm an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.95,0:08:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489956,489956}To make this play a success, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.32,0:08:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:494327,494327}Mr. Onodera.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.02,0:08:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:495028,495028}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.79,0:08:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:496796,496796}I'll trust you on this.\NIt's an actor's world on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.63,0:08:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:499632,499632}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:21.73,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:501735,501735}The second act has started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.27,0:08:24.27,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:504270,504270}Sitting in the lobby, Ayumi's heart was filled with a nervous feeling about Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.04,0:08:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:510043,510043}Please hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.64,0:08:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:512645,512645}Okay, I'll get a bunch of film, and we've got to take lots of pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.68,0:08:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:515682,515682}Great, why don't we have enough film at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.48,0:08:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:520487,520487}But, this Helen and Sullivan are really something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:524124,524124}I've never seen anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:49.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:529062,529062}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.63,0:08:51.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531631,531631}What did he mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.03,0:08:54.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534034,534034}What's going on\Nbehind those doors?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:539606,539606}Rei?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:11.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:551484,551484}Different.\NThis is different from practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.15,0:09:14.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:554154,554154}Mrs. Himekawa Utako.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.05,0:09:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:559059,559059}Here, Helen. I want you to understand that things have names.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.23,0:09:24.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:564230,564230}Helen.\NYes, I am Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.26,0:09:27.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:567267,567267}Whatever happens or changes,\NI am Helen on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.94,0:09:38.94,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:578945,578945}The two were no longer acting,\Nbut became real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.21,0:09:43.21,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:583216,583216}Maya became Helen, and, like her,\NUtako became Annie Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.22,0:09:53.22,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:593226,593226}Between them was a shared rhythm,\Nand they were even feeling a sense of connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.23,0:10:01.23,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:601234,601234}Finally, the climactic miracle scene came.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.70,0:10:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:604704,604704}Here, pump.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.84,0:10:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:606840,606840}No, pump.\NThis is water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:611011,611011}W·A·T·E·R.\NWater.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.81,0:10:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:614814,614814}This is its name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.40,0:10:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:634401,634401}Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.85,0:10:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:650850,650850}Wa… ter!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:02.69,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:662696,662696}The battle between Sullivan and Helen,\NUtako and Maya, was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.50,0:11:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:671504,671504}It's not over yet, it's a curtain call.\NOpen it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.12,0:11:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:694127,694127}Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:695829,695829}She didn't even kiss\Nher own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.47,0:11:49.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:709476,709476}Maya. You inspire me\Nto keep up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.91,0:11:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:717917,717917}Mr. Purple Rose, did you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.88,0:12:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:720887,720887}My Helen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.22,0:12:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:723223,723223}I might have given up\Nwithout your encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.43,0:12:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:732432,732432}Who?\NWho's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.60,0:12:16.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:736603,736603}Is it… Mr. Purple Rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.58,0:12:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:753586,753586}Mr. Purple Rose,\NI know you are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.72,0:12:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:759726,759726}Hello there, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.72,0:12:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:760727,760727}You.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.19,0:12:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:763196,763196}Are you looking\Nfor someone in a hurry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.79,0:12:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:765799,765799}I… I…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.56,0:12:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:767567,767567}He must be important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.76,0:12:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769769,769769}I know it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.87,0:12:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771871,771871}You really hate me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.94,0:12:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:773940,773940}When can you stop\Nmaking that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.47,0:12:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:778478,778478}The moment you see me…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:781848,781848}…you act as if you've seen a cockroach, centipede, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:15.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795962,795962}Kitajima Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:19.86,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:799866,799866}Maya and Utako's acting has received more\Nand more attention as the play continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.20,0:13:24.20,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:804204,804204}Ayumi's acting was also acclaimed\Nby the critics, but with Maya…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:30.37,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:810377,810377}…there was an unknown and unpredictable\Nelement that attracted the crowds.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.78,0:13:34.78,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:814781,814781}When Maya and Utako were on stage,\Ntheir in sync acts had no scripts or rehearsal…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.25,0:13:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:820253,820253}…and it was different every time they played.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.09,0:13:45.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:825091,825091}Mr. Purple Rose, Mother…\Nplease watch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:49.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:829396,829396}Can you hear that applause?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.53,0:13:53.53,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:833533,833533}Fukui Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.96,0:13:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:835969,835969}I hear it, I heart it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.17,0:13:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:838171,838171}I hear the applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.84,0:14:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:840840,840840}How are you feeling, Haru?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.07,0:14:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841074,841074}Oh, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.51,0:14:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:843510,843510}You seem well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.44,0:14:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:846446,846446}All thanks to you, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.61,0:14:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:849616,849616}To take care of me with no money or family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.35,0:14:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:853353,853353}Oh, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.98,0:14:15.98,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:855989,855989}Haru was taken to a hospital in Nagano after she was found passed out on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.89,0:14:21.89,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:861895,861895}She had lost her eyesight\Nfrom malnutrition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.06,0:14:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:866066,866066}Hmm?\NWhat's this scrap of paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:868968,868968}It's my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.56,0:14:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:869569,869569}Your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:872072,872072}She's my only daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.84,0:14:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:873840,873840}She's 16 now.\NShe loves to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.97,0:14:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:877977,877977}She ran away to be an actress, and I found her picture in a magazine for a play she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.55,0:14:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:885552,885552}I know it was a tiny role, but look!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.15,0:14:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:891157,891157}Isn't she pretty?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.79,0:14:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893793,893793}Oh, what a pretty girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.29,0:14:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:896296,896296}I'll be looking out for her in magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.33,0:14:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:899332,899332}Was that okay, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.03,0:15:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:903036,903036}You couldn't even see her face on that paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.74,0:15:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:906740,906740}Besides, you don't even know if she even exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.94,0:15:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:910944,910944}Shh. I know, but it's\Nthe best medicine for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.04,0:15:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:916049,916049}Maya…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.28,0:15:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919285,919285}I hear the applause.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.02,0:15:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:922022,922022}Your mother hears it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.45,0:15:23.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:923456,923456}Mother…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.49,0:15:24.49,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:924491,924491}"The Miracle Worker," which received great press coverage…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.19,0:15:28.19,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:928194,928194}…finally came to the last night\Nwith a heated audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.33,0:15:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931331,931331}Please, this is for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931865,931865}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.17,0:15:38.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:938171,938171}A purple rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.14,0:15:44.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:944144,944144}He's here, somewhere in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.37,0:15:46.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:946379,946379}Mr. Purple Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.89,0:15:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:959893,959893}He's somewhere in here.\NI have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.53,0:16:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:963530,963530}Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.00,0:16:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:969002,969002}Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:971871,971871}Did anyone see who threw\Nthis purple rose?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.17,0:16:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:975175,975175}That's the girl who played Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.04,0:16:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:978044,978044}Please, I want to find the man\Nwith the purple rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.41,0:16:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:981414,981414}I loved your Helen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.91,0:16:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:982916,982916}I came to see you five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.75,0:16:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983750,983750}Please sign my book!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:985752,985752}Please let me through!\NExcuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.98,0:16:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:988988,988988}I need to get through!\NExcuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.49,0:16:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:994494,994494}Please…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.20,0:16:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1003203,1003203}Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.17,0:16:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1012178,1012178}M-Mr. Hayami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.77,0:16:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1012779,1012779}Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.55,0:16:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1018551,1018551}Are you okay, Mr. Masumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.78,0:16:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1019786,1019786}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.28,0:17:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1022288,1022288}It just hit my shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.59,0:17:09.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1029596,1029596}Why did he… for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.89,0:17:11.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1031898,1031898}I thought he hated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.53,0:17:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1034534,1034534}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.86,0:17:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1035869,1035869}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.51,0:17:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1044511,1044511}I… I misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.98,0:17:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1046980,1046980}You might be a nice person, but I…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.91,0:17:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051918,1051918}Thank you for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.22,0:17:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1054220,1054220}For you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.42,0:17:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1058425,1058425}I can't let our product be injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1061461,1061461}The play has ended,\Nbut we still have two extra nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.43,0:17:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1068435,1068435}That's the way it is, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.63,0:17:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1071638,1071638}D-Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.40,0:17:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073406,1073406}Until this play is over,\NI won't be sick or injured!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.19,0:18:15.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1095195,1095195}He's always like that, a cold man.\NAlways.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.39,0:18:18.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1098398,1098398}He only cares about this theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.53,0:18:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1102535,1102535}Are you Kitajima Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.57,0:18:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1106573,1106573}Yes, I am. But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.24,0:18:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1109242,1109242}Just for twenty minutes,\Nin a coffee shop down the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.24,0:18:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1112245,1112245}We were impressed\Nwith your talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.91,0:18:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1119919,1119919}What? The main role?\NFor me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.62,0:18:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1122622,1122622}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.62,0:18:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124624,1124624}If you come to our studio,\Nwe have TV shows, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1129062,1129062}Yeah, as a start, how about a main role in this play.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.00,0:18:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1134000,1134000}Me for the main role?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.16,0:18:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1136169,1136169}It's not a bad story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.97,0:18:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1137971,1137971}You can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.94,0:19:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148948,1148948}I'll take the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.31,0:19:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151317,1151317}Really?\NThen let's hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.82,0:19:15.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155822,1155822}Oh shit, that's Hayami Masumi\Nfrom Metropolitan Entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.62,0:19:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1159626,1159626}E-Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.43,0:19:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1163430,1163430}I don't have anything to do with\NMetropolitan Entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.50,0:19:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1170503,1170503}You are so terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.30,0:19:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1173306,1173306}I was about to get the main role.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.17,0:19:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1176176,1176176}What right do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.38,0:19:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1180380,1180380}Always getting in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.38,0:19:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182382,1182382}Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.38,0:19:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1184384,1184384}Don't just jump\Nonto any good stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.61,0:19:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1186619,1186619}They were scouts\Nfrom a B-class production.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.65,0:19:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1189656,1189656}If you get involved with them,\Nyou'll look like a second class actress, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.22,0:19:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1194227,1194227}Remember that,\Nif you want to become a star.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.80,0:20:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1200800,1200800}It's my decision.\NPlease leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.27,0:20:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1204270,1204270}Was it your dream to become\Na second class actress?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.74,0:20:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1209743,1209743}Was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.98,0:20:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1213980,1213980}I thought you'd become an actress\Nwho'd make your mother proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.75,0:20:18.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218752,1218752}Mother…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.09,0:20:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1229095,1229095}Uhh, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1231064,1231064}Watch your act, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.60,0:20:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1234601,1234601}You've been nominated for Best Supporting Actress by the Academy Awards Stage Drama Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1239639,1239639}Best Supporting Actress?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.34,0:20:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1241341,1241341}You are the favorite one, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.51,0:20:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1243510,1243510}See you at the Academy Awards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.38,0:20:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1252385,1252385}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.38,0:20:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1254387,1254387}I've been nominated\Nfor Best Supporting Actress?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.92,0:20:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258925,1258925}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.72,0:21:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1261728,1261728}Yes.\NThank you for calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.69,0:21:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1265699,1265699}Oh, young lady, you've been\Nnominated for an Academy Award?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.77,0:21:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1271771,1271771}Young lady,\Nyou don't look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.74,0:21:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1276743,1276743}Young lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.51,0:21:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278511,1278511}I'm not the only nominee.\NThere are five.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.91,0:21:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1281915,1281915}The favored nominee is that girl,\NKitajima Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.75,0:21:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1285752,1285752}Don't misunderstand,\NI don't care about the award.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.49,0:21:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1290490,1290490}But the public has chosen her as the best actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.96,0:21:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1294961,1294961}It must be a mistake, young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.69,0:21:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1297697,1297697}It's only natural that you will get the award.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.23,0:21:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301234,1301234}Mama… never kissed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.10,0:21:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307107,1307107}I did all I can,\Nand I don't have any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.94,0:21:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1311945,1311945}I played Helen\Nas perfect as I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.08,0:21:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1314080,1314080}You're right. All the critics said\Nhow perfect your acting was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.45,0:22:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1321454,1321454}But Mama has seen more potential\Nin her as an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.82,0:22:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1325825,1325825}Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.62,0:22:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1327627,1327627}That's why she kissed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.09,0:22:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1329095,1329095}Young lady…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.03,0:22:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332032,1332032}I want to know…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.16,0:22:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1334167,1334167}…what made her the better actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.87,0:22:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1337871,1337871}What's the difference between her and I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.71,0:22:24.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1344711,1344711}I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.91,0:22:26.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1346913,1346913}I'm the favored candidate?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.71,0:22:29.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1349716,1349716}I can't believe it…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.85,0:22:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1353853,1353853}Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.22,0:22:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1358224,1358224}Mother…!
